description: Sets the Firewall Manager policy administrator as a tenant administrator of a third-party firewall service. A tenant is an instance of the third-party firewall service that's associated with your Amazon Web Services customer account.

parameters.name: ThirdPartyFirewall
parameters.description: The name of the third-party firewall vendor.

nested_items.name: ThirdPartyFirewallStatus
nested_items.description: The current status for setting a Firewall Manager policy administrator's account as an administrator of the third-party firewall tenant.
ONBOARDING - The Firewall Manager policy administrator is being designated as a tenant administrator.
ONBOARD_COMPLETE - The Firewall Manager policy administrator is designated as a tenant administrator.
OFFBOARDING - The Firewall Manager policy administrator is being removed as a tenant administrator.
OFFBOARD_COMPLETE - The Firewall Manager policy administrator has been removed as a tenant administrator.
NOT_EXIST - The Firewall Manager policy administrator doesn't exist as a tenant administrator.
